{"id":33524,"date":"2019-09-16T14:30:24","date_gmt":"2019-09-16T10:30:24","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=33524"},"modified":"2019-09-16T14:30:24","modified_gmt":"2019-09-16T10:30:24","slug":"good-luck-charms-idolatry","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/09\/16\/good-luck-charms-idolatry\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Amulets: Wearing good luck charms an act of idolatry"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>\u2018Uqbah ibn \u2018Amir reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, received a group of men and he accepted the pledge of nine of them, while he refrained from one. They said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, you accepted the pledge of nine men and left this one out?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Verily, there is an amulet upon him.<\/strong>\u201d The man took it in his hand and cut it, then the Prophet accepted his pledge and he said, \u201c<strong>Whoever hangs an amulet around his neck has committed an act of idolatry.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 17388<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064f\u0642\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0645\u0650\u0631\u064d \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0642\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0644\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0631\u064e\u0647\u0652\u0637\u064c \u0641\u064e\u0628\u064e\u0627\u064a\u064e\u0639\u064e \u062a\u0650\u0633\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0629\u064b \u0648\u064e\u0623\u064e\u0645\u0652\u0633\u064e\u0643\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0648\u064